Privacy Policy â€“ Vid Player
Last updated: 22/01/2026
Vid Player respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our application.
Vid Player is an offline video player designed to play media files stored on your device.
Information We Collect
Vid Player does not collect any personal information such as name, email address, phone number, or location.
The app may access:
Local media files (videos) for playback only
Basic non-personal device information such as device model, Android version, and crash logs for app improvement
No media files are uploaded or shared with any server.
Permissions
The app uses only required permissions:
Media access for video playback
Storage access (via Android Scoped Storage / MediaStore) for features like rename, move, or delete
No unnecessary permissions are requested.
Use of Information
Any collected non-personal information is used only to:
Improve app performance
Fix bugs and crashes
Enhance user experience
We do not sell, share, or transfer user data to third parties.
Third-Party Services
Vid Player may use third-party services such as analytics or crash reporting, which have their own privacy policies.
Data Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your data. However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure.
Childrenâ€™s Privacy
Vid Player does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under the age of 13.
Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected on this page.
